      <bioghist>
         <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
         <p>Amos B. Stanton of Adrian, N.Y. (Steuben County) served as a 1st lieutenant in the 86th Regiment, New York Volunteers, an Elmira, N.Y. regiment. He was killed at Petersburg on June 16, 1864.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Primarily Civil War letters from Stanton to his wife. Also, family letters, certificates, pension files, clippings, publications, and diaries of John Crosby and Amos B. Stanton.</p>
      </scopecontent>
